What's happening now? 

If you're wondering why the Canadian government spent 4.5 billion dollars to buy a 60-year-old pipeline with a penchant for springing leaks, so are we. 
You can read more about what's happening now here: 
https://www.nationalobserver.com/2018/06/12/news/leaked-letter-reveals-kinder-morgan-broke-rules-months-canadian-officials-noticed

Did you know? 

What impact do we, as humans, have on our planet? Not a good one, apparently. A recent study shows that humans, who make up just 0.01% of all life on Earth has destroyed 83% of all wild mammals. 
Find out more here:
https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2018/may/21/human-race-just-001-of-all-life-but-has-destroyed-over-80-of-wild-mammals-study

Something to think about

What is an animal's place in a human-dominated world? Michael Pollan takes on the meat industry and the horrifying conditions of the industrial animal farm. 
You can read the whole article here:
https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/10/magazine/an-animal-s-place.html

Reality check!

Are you recycling? If so, are you doing it right? From washing out food-covered containers to recycling batteries, here are the 10 most common recycling mistakes being made.
