CHALLENGES 

Get in touch with your political representatives. Walk to their constituency office, send an email, or give them a call. Let them know that you expect real climate action. 
Then take a picture and share it on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram with #Catalystree because the world deserves to know how awesome you are!
More on this here: https://www.coastprotectors.ca/

Commit to #MeatlessMondays. It might be hard to give up meat but 18% of greenhouse gas emissions come from the meat and dairy industry and that's not okay. 
Then take a picture and share it on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram with #Catalystree because the world deserves to know how awesome you are!
More on this here: https://www.cnn.com/2017/04/08/opinions/go-vegan-save-the-planet-wang/index.html

Choose sustainable transportation. Pick one day this week to leave the car at home. Walk, take the bus, or carpool. 
Then take a picture and share it on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram with #Catalystree because the world deserves to know how awesome you are!
More on this here: https://bcgreencare.ca/carpooling-has-big-impact

Reduce and reuse before you recycle. Choose one eco-friendly alternative this week, whether that's using reusuable bags or just shopping at a local farmer's market
Then take a picture and share it on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram with #Catalystree because the world deserves to know how awesome you are!
Looking for inspiration? Check this out: http://www.therogueginger.com/

Are you recycling right? Take a few minutes this week to read this article (http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/recycling-contamination-1.4606893?cmp=FB_Post_News) and see if there are any adjustments you need to make to your recycling regime. 
Then take a picture and share it on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram with #Catalystree because the world deserves to know how awesome you are!



